
What is a WebElement
anything we see on the web page is considered to be a web element

HTML?
HyperText Markup Language

What is DOM (Document Object Model)?
Browsers internal view of the webpage
INternale view of the webpage
Also called as developers tools or dev tools
Document-->a simple html document which represents the page we are inspecting
Object-->any line in html is considered to be an Object
Model-->it is just a layout of the html

in order to work with objects in selenium we need to identify the locators.

A locator is an address or a position of a webelement on the webpage. It is used to locate or identify webelements on the webpage.
(shows the locations of the elements we want to interact with.)

8 locators:
1. ID
2. Name
3. Tag Name
4. xPath
5. LinkText
6. PartialLinkText
7. CssSelectors
8. ClassName

Everytime you try to locate an element always look for the ID first cause it is unique

Why do we need so many locators?
-developers may not provide all the locators for all the elements
-some locators may have duplicate values in different nodes
-some locators may not be applicable for the elements are looking for
e.g linktext and partialLinkText are only used for links

"a" tag is also called an anchor tag

if 2 or more elements have same attributes and attribute values selenium will only